@node "Inst" "Installation"

 There is no commodore installer script included because installing
 YAA is easy. (see below)

 @{b}MANUAL INSTALLATION@{ub}

 - Copy the YAA executeable to an appropriate place.
   (also the Amigaguide document of you like).
 - Copy your keyfile to L:

 It does no need any extra files, apart from libraries. (See @{"Requirements" link "reqs"})

 If you are upgrading from AddressSearch  then you should use the supplied
 YAAconvert program to convert from the old fileformat to the new.

@endnode


@node "Manu" How to use"

 @{b}HOW TO USE@{ub}

 There are three executeables included in this archive.

 One is called YAA, this is the main program and you can search and edit records
 with this program.

 The second is called YAAsearch, this is a search only program. You cannot edit
 records with this program. This was written to use less memory.

 The last is YAAdisksearch, this is will not load the records into memory, but
 instead each time you search for an entry it will do so direct from disk.


 1. Start YAA by clicking on the icon.
    YAA can be run from CLI, but the tooltypes will not be used.

 2. If the @{b}CX_POPUP@{ub} tooltype is set to @{b}YES@{ub} or it is run from CLI then
    the GUI will appear, else the hotkey can can pressed. (See @{b}CX_POPKEY@{ub}
    tooltype).

 Clicking on the close gadget will hide the program.


 @{b}ADDING A RECORD@{ub}

 1. All adding and editing is done with the 'Update' window, so click on 'Update'.
 2. Enter the details into the relevant string gadgets (Press 'New' to start
    with a fresh set of gadgets).
 3. When ready to add the record click on 'Add'.
    If you decide that you don't want to add the record then click 'Quit',
    'New' or whatever you want to do.

 @{b}EDITING A RECORD@{ub}

 1. Either use 'Find', 'Jump', or 'Next'/'Previous to display the record to
    edit.
 2. Edit the strings as you like.
 3. Click on 'Update' to update the record.
    If you decide not to update the changes then don't click on 'Update'.

 @{b}ERASING A RECORD@{ub}

 1. Either use 'Find', 'Jump', or 'Next'/'Previous to display the record to
    erase.
 2. Click on `Erase' to erase the record.


 @{b}CLEARING ALL RECORDS FROM MEMORY@{ub}

 1. In the main window click @{b}Load@{ub}
 2. In the ReqTools requester click @{b}Cancel@{ub}
 3. You will be asked if you want to remove all records. Click @{b}OK@{ub}



 @{b}MAIN WINDOW GADGETS@{ub}

  @{b}Find@{ub}
   A reqtools requester will appear in the centre of the screen.
   You type some text (a string), the program will search through all the
   records until one contains that string in any field.
   Remember that the option Case Sensitive will affect the search.
   When the program finds a record it will display the information and you
   have a choice of Searching again or cancelling the search.
   @{B}You can also type "*" in the reqtools requester and this will mean that
   each record will be shown in turn.@{ub}

  @{b}Update@{ub}
   This will bring up a window with several string gadgets and buttons.
   @{"Update window gadgets" link "update"}    

  @{b}Save@{ub}
   This will save all the records into a file.
   If Encryption is set in the preferences/tooltypes then a password will be
   prompted for. You will need to enter this twice.
   The password must be 10 characters or less.

  @{b}Load@{ub}
   This will load a file of records.
   If the file is encrypted then you will need to enter the password.

  @{b}Prefs@{ub}
   Another window will appear.
   Currently you can only save these options using @{"ToolTypes" link "opti"}.
   @{"Prefs window gadgets" link "prefs"}

  @{b}Quit@{ub}
   This will quit the program.



 @{b}UPDATE WINDOW GADGETS@{ub}

  @{b}Add@{ub}
   This will take the text from the string gadgets and create a record.

  @{b}Update@{ub}
   This will take the text from the string gadgets and overwrite the current
   record.
   You will be prompted with the name of the old record to be overwritten.

  @{b}Erase@{ub}
   This will delete the current record.
   You will be prompted with the name of the current record to be deleted.

  @{b}New@{ub}
   This will clear all the string gadgets.
   @{b}Note:@{ub} This does not delete the record unless you click on @{b}Update@{ub}

  @{b}Find@{ub}
   A reqtools requester will appear in the centre of the screen.
   You type some text (a string), the program will search through all the
   records until one contains that string in any field.
   Remember that the option Case Sensitive will affect the search.
   @{b}You can also type "*" in the reqtools requester and this will mean that
   each record will be shown in turn.@{b}

   When the program finds a record it will display the information and you
   have a choice of Searching again or Editing the record, which will change
   the gadgets to the chosen record.

  @{b}Next@{ub}
   This will change the current record and the gadgets to the next record.

  @{b}Previous@{ub}
   This will change the current record and the gadgets to the previous
   record.

  @{b}Jump@{ub}
   This will bring a reqtools requester.
   You need to enter a value, the program will then jump straight to that record.

  @{b}Quit@{ub}
   This will take you back to the main window.
@endnode


@node "prefs" "Prefs"

 @{b}PREFS WINDOW GADGETS@{ub}

  @{b}Case Sense@{ub}
   Will mean that when you search the case of each letter is used.

  @{b}Save encrypted@{ub}
   Will mean that your files are saved with a password and this password will
   be needed to read it.
   If you encrypt a file and forget the password I can help you. (See Author
   information).
   You do not need to have this checked to load encrypted files.
   The password must be 8 characters or less.

  @{b}Duplicate checking@{ub}
   Means that if you add a record that has either the same Name or Company
   name then it will ask you if you still want to add it.
   I suggest you leave this on.

  @{b}Create .bak@{ub}
   Will rename the file to be overwritten as <filename>.bak if you choose to
   save over an existing file.

  @{b}Capitalise first char@{ub}
   If you want the first letter of each word automatically converted to uppercase
   check this option.
@endnode


@node "Opti" "ToolTypes"

 @{b}TOOLTYPES@{ub}

 @{b}CXPOPUP=YES|NO@{ub}
 If set to yes then the main window will appear.

 @{b}CXPOPKEY=popkey@{ub}
 This is the keys to press in order to make the program appear when hidden.

 @{b}MAXRECORDS=number@{ub} (not available in YAAdisksearch)
 To save memory or gain access to unlimited records you can specify here the
 maximum number of records that you can create/load etc.
 If you you are not able to create a new record or load an existing file
 because there are too many records then increase this.
 Default is 200 (records).

 @{b}SCREEN=screenname@{ub}
 This is the name of the screen to open on.

 @{b}WINPOSX=number@{ub}
 The window will appear number pixels from the left of the screen.

 @{b}WINPOSY=number@{ub}
 The window will appear number pixels from the top of the screen.

 @{b}WINWIDTH=number@{ub}
 This program contains a fairly basic font sensitive GUI, however when it comes
 to making sure all the text fits on nicely from the start of a sentence to the
 end you can increase the width with this tooltype.
 Default is 254 (pixels)

 @{b}FONTNAME=name.font@{ub}
 Instead of using the default workbench font you can specify here your own choice
 of font. For example 'FONTNAME=Helvetica.font'.

 @{b}FONTSIZE=number@{ub}
 This tooltype sets the fontsize of FONTNAME to load and use. For example
 'FONTSIZE=11'.

 @{b}FILEPATH=path@{ub}
 This is the default path for loading/saving files.

 @{b}LOADFILE=filename@{ub}
 This will attempt to the load the specified file.
 Remember to include the path as part of the filename.

 @{b}CASESENSE=ON|OFF@{ub}
 This turns case sense on or off.

 @{b}ENCRYPTION=ON|OFF@{ub} (not available in YAAsearch and YAAdisksearch)
 This is turns encryption on or off.

 @{b}DUPLICHECK=ON|OFF@{ub} (not available in YAAsearch and YAAdisksearch)
 This turns Duplicate checking on or off. (See @{"Prefs window gadgets" link "prefs"})

 @{b}CREATEBAK=YES|NO@{ub} (not available in YAAsearch and YAAdisksearch)
 This will either create a .bak file when you choose to overwrite an existing
 file.

 @{b}CAPITALISE=YES|NO@{ub} (not available in YAAsearch and YAAdisksearch)
 If you don't want the first character of every word capitalised automatically
 then set CAPITALISE to NO.
@endnode


@node "Hist" "History"

 @{b}THE HISTORY OF YAA@{ub}

 - version 1.0  (03-11-96)  -  Initial public release
 - version 1.0a             -  Registered user update
                               - Fixed gadgetlist attachment bug
 - version 1.0b             -  Internal update.
 - version 1.1  (19-03-98)  -  Second public release
                               - Optimisations, most code rewritten
                               - Devised new save format, much smaller and quicker
                               - Added user definable font
                               - Nearly font sensitive GUI
                               - Fixed 'Jump' button
                               - A password of 8 chars would cause a crash - fixed
                               - Added tooltypes: MAXRECORDS, FONTNAME,
                                 FONTSIZE, WINWIDTH, CAPITALISE.
                               - Tidied up windows and buttons
@endnode


